# IndiaMART Integration Project Structure

This is a Node.js project for IndiaMART LMS CRM Integration v2 with AI-based quote management capabilities.

## Project Organization

- **Source Code**: [src/](mdc:src/) - Core application modules
  - [src/index.js](mdc:src/index.js) - Main entry point exporting all components
  - [src/indiamart-client.js](mdc:src/indiamart-client.js) - Core API client
  - [src/response-handler.js](mdc:src/response-handler.js) - Response processing
  - [src/api-compliance.js](mdc:src/api-compliance.js) - Rate limiting and compliance
  - [src/error-handler.js](mdc:src/error-handler.js) - Error handling and classification
  - [src/polling-service.js](mdc:src/polling-service.js) - Automated lead fetching
  - [src/polling-config.js](mdc:src/polling-config.js) - Configuration management
  - [src/types.d.ts](mdc:src/types.d.ts) - TypeScript definitions

- **Tests**: [tests/](mdc:tests/) - Comprehensive test suite
  - [tests/test.js](mdc:tests/test.js) - Unit tests
  - [tests/compliance-test.js](mdc:tests/compliance-test.js) - Compliance tests
  - [tests/date-format-test.js](mdc:tests/date-format-test.js) - Date format tests
  - [tests/error-test.js](mdc:tests/error-test.js) - Error handling tests
  - [tests/response-example.js](mdc:tests/response-example.js) - Response processing tests

- **Examples**: [examples/](mdc:examples/) - Ready-to-run applications
  - [examples/example.js](mdc:examples/example.js) - Basic usage example
  - [examples/polling-example.js](mdc:examples/polling-example.js) - Polling service demo
  - [examples/start-polling.js](mdc:examples/start-polling.js) - CLI polling launcher
  - [examples/monitor-polling.js](mdc:examples/monitor-polling.js) - Service monitoring

- **Documentation**: [docs/](mdc:docs/) - Project documentation
  - [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Main documentation
  - [PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md](mdc:PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md) - Structure guide

## Key Configuration Files

- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project configuration and scripts
- [.env](mdc:.env) - Environment variables (not in git)
- [.env.example](mdc:.env.example) - Environment template
- [.gitignore](mdc:.gitignore) - Git ignore rules

## Import Patterns

- From root: `import { IndiaMartClient } from './src/indiamart-client.js'`
- From src/: `import { IndiaMartClient } from './indiamart-client.js'`
- Main entry: `import { IndiaMartClient } from './src/index.js'`